paragraphs.title: Introduction
paragraphs.text:
%md
This notebook will show you different ways to explore the dataset. We will use Pyspark API. 
The dataset used for the analysis is from California Air Resources Board. The original dataset can be downloaded from  https://www.arb.ca.gov/emfac/2014/. The dataset contains different vehicle types and the emissions for the different calendar years. For this analysis, the California Statewide annualized emissions dataset is used.

paragraphs.title: Step 5B: Filtering Data w/ Parameterized Input
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
stw_ann_agg.filter(stw_ann_agg.Speed == z.input("Speed in multiples of 5")).filter(stw_ann_agg.VehClass == z.input("Vehicle Class")).show()

paragraphs.title: Step 5B: Filtering Data w/ Dropdown Menu
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
stw_ann_agg.filter(stw_ann_agg.VehClass == z.select("Vehicle Class", [("T7 NOOS","T7 Neighboring Out of State"), ("T7 NNOOS","T7 Non Neighboring Out of State")])).show()
